title: PPPP’s Murad Ali Shah wins PS-77 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Murad Ali Shah has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-77 Jamshoro-I by securing 74,613 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Roshan Ali Buriro of Grand Democratic Alliance (GDA) who bagged 10,268 votes.
Voters’ turn-out remained 53.44%.
